#Prerequisites for c++ code on windows:#
*Microsoft Visual Studio 2015 or highter
*Boost C++ Libraries http://www.boost.org



Steps to fulfill the pre-requisites on a Windows laptop:

Download the community version from here: https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/

Download the vcpkg manager (It will install boost) from here:

Open Visual Basic Developed Command Prompt. Go to the vcpkg folder. Perform the following steps

Remember that Microsoft Visual Studio offers 32 bit (x86) version. So, any 64 bit (x64) installation via vcpkg will not work. For more information, read this:

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44360738/how-to-install-visual-studio-2017-64bit-version-explicitly

